                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, Oct. 1: Tata Motors today launched an institutional share sale offer to raise over Rs 2,300 crore ($525 million). Tata Motors intends to use the proceeds to reduce debts, increase capital expenditure and for long-term capital requirements among other things, a company statement said. It also said shareholders through a postal ballot on August 10 had approved the offer. The shares are proposed to be listed on both the BSE and the NSE.                            
	 New York, Oct. 1: Technology giant Hewlett-Packard has appointed German software firm SAP AGs former executive Leo Apotheker as its new chief executive officer and president. Apotheker, who will succeed the companys interim CEO Cathie Lesjak, will also join HPs board of directors, the company said in a statement.                                                                                                                          
